<H3> <TI>   Yangbajain Geothermal Deep Well Project Passes Appraisal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yangbajain Geothermal Deep Well Project Passes Appraisal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94P60202 Chengdu SICHUAN RIBAO in Chinese 25 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> 94P60202 </F>
<F P=104>  Chengdu SICHUAN RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

  [Text] On 15 March, the "Xizang Yangbajain Geothermal Deep 
Well" project passed appraisal by the China Energy Expert 
Committee in Qiaoxia County. 
  Xizang is rich in geothermal resources and data support 
State energy development criteria for the creation of 
10,000-kilowatt-class geothermal electric power plants. The 
Yangbajain deep well project would make use of a single-unit 
12,000-kilowatt geothermal power plant that draws on deep-well 
high-temperature, high-energy underground heat sources. The 
project could be completed and in operation in 1995. 

</TEXT>

